    "In chronic loneliness, people are no longer able to assess their condition concerning (rememberable) experiences of closeness, affective resonance, existential security, and closeness to others.",
    "This can include a reduced capability to interpret social cues correctly, i.e., it is not solely because they are lonely that people are shunned, but also because they might display altered recognition of others, for instance, due to their anticipation of being rejected (81).",
